{
  "texts": [
    "Finally, we fine-tuned the pre-trained DeBERTa encoder (He et al., 2021) on these combined datasets.",
    "This model detects hallucinations based on the semantic relationship between the document and summary.",
    "Span-based detection NLI provides sentence-or summary-level hallucination detection, while NER is restricted to a predefined set of named entities.",
    "To explore a more general fine-grained hallucination detection, we train a token-level hallucination detection model to provide more detailed AI feedback, such as highlighting hallucinated text spans.",
    "Starting with the dataset labeled by GPT-4 for the NLI model, as described in Section 3.2, we further ask GPT-4 to highlight the hallucinated text spans if the text contains hallucinations."
  ]
}